ElementDescription: How often did you drink alcohol?
Notes: 1=Less than once a month but at least once in the past 12 months; 2=One to three times a month; 3=One to two times a week; 4=More than twice a week; 5=Every day; 6=Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: On a typical drinking occasion, how much did you usually drink
Notes: 1=Usually no more than 1 drink; 2=Usually no more than 2 drinks; 3=Usually no more than 3 drinks; 4=Usually 4 or more drinks; 5=Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: What is the greatest number of drinks that you had in any single day?
Notes: 1=1 drink; 2=2 drinks; 3=3 drinks; 4=4 or more drinks; 5=Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: How often did you have 4 or more drinks in a single day?
Notes: 1=Less than once a month but at least once in the past 12 months; 2=One to three times a month; 3=One to two times a week; 4=More than twice a week; 5=Every day; 6=Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: How often did you drink to the point of intoxication or drunkenness (e.g., drinking noticeably affected your thinking, talking, and behavior; feeling dizzy, ill, or out of control; or passing out; etc.)?
Notes: 1=I never drank to the point of being drunk in the past 12 months; 2= Less than once a month but at least once in the past 12 months; 3=One to three times a month; 4=One to two times a week; 5=More than twice a week; 6=Every day; 7=Prefer not to answer
